<br>
On the other hand..<br>
<br>
Many targets are often already rooted, specially in Caster Heavy groups/servers. Often root is used as a means to give a caster who has someone on him (or close to on him) some running space. Because of this, by the time you get there and able to get off PF, the targets immunity timer to that CC is in place. This leaves the skill virtually useless in encounters with a lot of Root CC.<br>
<br>
A common complaint amongst shield users is the same principal as this. Shield slam, the anytime 8 second long stun, is on the same immunity timer as castable stun. Again, magic heavy groups/servers often have targets getting stunned quickly and frequently. By the time a shield user is allowed the oppertunity to slam, the targets CC immunity timer is in effect, and again renders a skill useless.<br>
<br>
I personally do not know which one I side with; being a mercenary without PF, I rely on casters to watch out for themselves, or have classes that are appropriate to the job fill the role. However, having to dish out a skill that costs 14 points and could be considered useless makes me believe that it should not be on an immunity timer with all the others (my server has a balance of magic/melee. Even so, all forms of CC are often used per battle). Raising a shield reaver, I believe i'll have leaned more twords making it on its own CC once he gets Slam. <p>&quot;We will never be what Mythic promised we would when DAoC started, we might as well adapt or delete.&quot; -Avandor<br>
Lothire - 50 Mercenary<br>
